title: Week 6 NFL Recap: Packers quit vs Bucs, Kyle Shanahan's genius on display, Browns look terrible (Football 10/19)
description:
Will Brinson, Ryan Wilson and John Breech join together (on Zoom) to recap all the Sunday action from Week 6 of the 2020 NFL season. The best games on paper turned out to be not that interesting at all as Aaron Rodgers' touchdown celebration backfired against Tom Brady and the Bucs and Baker Mayfield and the Browns were a no show vs. the Steelers. Full slate breakdown below.
Bucs-Packers (:30)
49ers-Rams (11:45)
Steelers-Browns (23:45)
Express (32:15)
Ravens-Eagles (34:00)
Broncos-Patriots (47:00)
Titans-Texans (53:20)
Colts-Bengals (1:04:45)
Falcons-Vikings (1:13:30)
Lions-Jaguars (1:19:00)
Bears-Panthers (1:24:45)
Giants-Washington (1:30:00)
Dolphins-Jets (1:33:30)
Winners/Losers (1:38:00)
'Pick Six' is available on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, Stitcher, Google Podcasts, Castbox and wherever else you listen to podcasts.
